snippet.textDisplay: The best part about coke studio is giving 90's kids an opportunity to get to know our roots, our language and a breadth of our traditions. The more you listen to pure Punjabi/Urdu, the more you fall in love with it. So beautiful, deep and meaningful Punjabi/Urdu actually is. Could be just us natives but I simply cannot find depth of "Rus na saanwal yaar, mudataan beet gyaan" in English or any other language. Epic combination of  western and south asian music. Big fan of Krewella sisters. Well done!
